Text:
All songs 29 seconds, in 22khz mono 8bit.

Most new cellphones will happily accept 16bit, mono, 44,1khz 64kbps MP3 files. And at least one minute.

Decent songs however.

Well they sound considerably better in that format, and makes the high pitched notes more audible.

Such a big difference it's unbearable on my Motorola.
